No fewer than 18 personal aides have been appointed by Yahaya Bajoga, the councillor representing Bajoga East in Funakaye Local Government Area of Gombe State, saying that politics is not about making money. Our correspondent reports that the viral notice of appointment include a Principal Private Secretary, 12 special assistants, and five personal assistants. Bagoja, who also serves as chairman of Gombe Councillors’ Forum, an umbrella body of councillors from 114 wards of the state, said the appointment would help spread the dividends of democracy to his people. He noted that his interest in politics was due to his quest to alleviate the sufferings of his people, noting that he had attracted other projects aside employment. Yusuf, a successful businessman, says he is presently in tertiary institution, adding that education is key. “I’m a Sociology undergraduate of University of Maiduguri. I’m not rich but my salary is enough to settle the number appointed because politics should not be about making money but the impact on people,” Yusuf said. Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com